						               													<description>This game consists of 6 small games for children to start learning letters and reading.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game 1 - Insert letters:&amp;#10;The children insert letter tiles in the correct alphabetical order in the frame. This can be controlled with the ABC board. For correct letters, the kid gets a mouse cards and the one with the most mouse cards wins at the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game 2 - Arrange letters&amp;#10;The letter tiles are put face down in the frame above the ABC board according to color. The starting kid roles the dice and one letter card of the corresponding colour is revealed which s/he needs to put in the correct place.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game 3- Guessing letters&amp;#10;The letters are put unordered in the cheese frame, underneath is a template sheet (inserted by a child as the game leader). Whoever thinks they can guess the letter quickly puts their mouse on it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game 4 - Search for a word&amp;#10;The letters are placed face down in the frame. The game master selects a word from the word list and the children try to find the letters of this word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game 5 - Reveal a word&amp;#10;The letters of a word from the list are to be found and uncovered in one go, everyone has to remember all the uncovered letters and their places.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game 6 - Find a word&amp;#10;Words are to be formed from the revealed letters. The children can use the word list to help them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
